1
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:39,400
<i> I don't want to lose you, Dad.</i>

2
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:41,300
<i> You will never lose me.</i>

3
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:45,267
<i>But Mommy said, if you fix
things with your family,</i>

4
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,133
<i> I'll be out of the picture.</i>

5
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,400
<i> Trust me, okay?</i>

6
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:49,667
<i> What did he promise you?</i>

7
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:50,800
<i> That he'd fight for you?</i>

8
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,233
<i>You'll be thrown away,
like garbage.</i>

9
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:53,267
<i> Dad loves me.</i>

10
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,400
<i>He'll protect me,
he'll fight for me, Mom!</i>

11
00:00:55,533 --> 00:00:56,633
<i> Who are you so proud of?</i>

12
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:57,733
<i> Your dad?</i>

13
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:59,933
<i>You really think he'd still
fight for you</i>

14
00:01:00,067 --> 00:01:02,833
<i>even after he finds out
you're not his real child?</i>

15
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:04,600
<i>I had to make Manuel
take responsibility.</i>

16
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:06,600
<i>There are laws in Saudi Arabia.</i>

17
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:10,200
<i>A woman can't be pregnant
if she's not married.</i>

18
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:11,533
<i> That's why I trapped Manuel...</i>

19
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:13,633
<i> I trapped him into marriage!</i>

20
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:14,533
<i> No.</i>

21
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:20,167
<i> No!</i>

22
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:23,933
<i> That's not true!</i>

23
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:30,067
<i> Jeffrey, I miss you!</i>

24
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:32,733
<i> Jeff!</i>

25
00:01:32,867 --> 00:01:34,100
<i> Son.</i>

26
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,867
<i> Jeff.</i>

27
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,400
<i> Dear, please help me.</i>

28
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:41,567
<i>Don't let the annulment
push through.</i>

29
00:01:41,733 --> 00:01:43,633
<i> You do it your own!</i>

30
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,633
<i> Will you help me?</i>

31
00:01:47,767 --> 00:01:50,300
<i>Or should I tell your dad
the truth</i>

32
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:53,233
<i>that he raised a child
who isn't even his?</i>

33
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:54,767
<i>- Son.
- Get out of here!</i>

34
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,000
I said leave!

35
00:02:12,133 --> 00:02:13,667
Jeff, it's me.

36
00:02:26,533 --> 00:02:32,167
Jeff, thank you for coming back,
even with Dad here.

37
00:02:35,267 --> 00:02:36,767
I didn't really have a choice.

38
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:41,833
I didn't have anywhere else
to go.

39
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:45,567
Because if I stayed alone
in that apartment,

40
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:47,033
I think I'd go crazy.

41
00:02:49,367 --> 00:02:51,500
So I'll just endure it.

42
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:53,433
Your dad's leaving soon anyway.

43
00:02:58,233 --> 00:02:59,667
I'm here, Jeff.

44
00:03:01,567 --> 00:03:03,867
You can pour everything out
on me.

45
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:12,133
Your anger, your pain,
your sadness.

46
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:14,800
I'm going to bug you, Jeff.

47
00:03:14,933 --> 00:03:17,000
Make you laugh.

48
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:19,067
Do whatever I can
to make you happy.

49
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,833
You know, you're trying to
compete with me in crying.

50
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:27,700
I'm the one crying here.

51
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,533
- It hasn't even started yet.
- Come here.

52
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:39,267
I hope Andrea comes back.

53
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:44,700
I wish things could go back
to the way they were, Jeff.

54
00:03:46,967 --> 00:03:48,667
I miss us.

55
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:02,033
Does Andrea know what happened?

56
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,300
She doesn't know yet.

57
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,033
Where's Jessica?

58
00:04:22,167 --> 00:04:24,300
She said she's still
on her way home.

59
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:26,033
Hey.

60
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:28,300
Let's wait for the kids first.

61
00:04:28,467 --> 00:04:29,267
No, it's fine.

62
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,333
I'll just eat in the room.

63
00:04:30,467 --> 00:04:32,167
Jeff might feel awkward
if I stay.

64
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,000
Wow!

65
00:04:40,133 --> 00:04:42,867
Mom really went all out
with the welcome.

66
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,567
Look at all this food.

67
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,700
Come on.

68
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:08,533
Coleen, let's eat.

69
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:09,633
Didang.

70
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,233
Are you okay, Mom?

71
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,867
Let's pray first, sweetie.

72
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,500
In the name of the Father,
the Son, the Holy Spirit, Amen.

73
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:26,500
Lord, thank You for the
food on the table today.

74
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:28,767
Thank You, too,
for all the blessings.

75
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:33,833
And thank You because
Jeff is finally home.

76
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,933
We're together again
as a family.

77
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:41,167
Lord, I hope Andrea
comes back soon, too.

78
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,733
Thank You.

79
00:05:42,867 --> 00:05:44,367
In Jesus's name...

80
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:47,867
- Amen.
- Amen.

81
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,100
Let's eat.

82
00:05:49,233 --> 00:05:49,900
Thank you.

83
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:51,833
Go on and eat.

84
00:05:51,967 --> 00:05:53,700
Here you go.

85
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,167
Okay.

86
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,200
Give Jeff some.

87
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,033
Mom, here.

88
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:04,533
Thank you, Didang.

89
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,933
Why did you tell her?

90
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:15,967
You guarded that secret
for eighteen years,

91
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:19,600
and then you just blurted it out
to Jessica?

92
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,833
I'm out of bullets.

93
00:06:21,967 --> 00:06:24,133
There's another war coming.

94
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:26,267
Manuel's going to
file for an annulment.

95
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,067
What?

96
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:29,033
On what grounds?

97
00:06:29,167 --> 00:06:32,000
Psychological incapacity.

98
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:34,333
So, I'm desperate.

99
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:36,500
That's why I told
Jessica the truth.

100
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:38,000
So I'd have something
to scare her with,

101
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:40,767
that her father could be
taken away from her.

102
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,200
And so she'd do whatever
she has to do

103
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:44,233
to protect our family.

104
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,267
But what if your plan backfires?

105
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,233
What if she tells Manuel?

106
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:52,933
Friend, you'd just hand
Manuel a loaded gun.

107
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:54,567
Your own husband.

108
00:06:56,033 --> 00:06:58,300
That won't happen.

109
00:06:58,433 --> 00:07:00,400
I know Jessica.

110
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,367
She loves her father
with all her heart.

111
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,833
He's practically her life.

112
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:06,867
She can never do that.

113
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,200
She will never do that.

114
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:09,567
She won't say a thing.

115
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,433
She's scared that the
whole truth will come out.

116
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:19,800
What about Jessica's real dad,
Jojo?

117
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:22,533
What if my godchild
decides to look for him?

118
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:28,567
Alice, it's been two decades
since that bastard ghosted me.

119
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,833
For all we know,
he's already dead.

120
00:07:30,967 --> 00:07:33,967
Literally a ghost now.

121
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:36,733
Let's go.

122
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,033
Maybe someone wants
to try my catfish?

123
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:46,067
Because, I swear,

124
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,333
I risked my life for those
at the market earlier!

125
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:50,433
Those three practically
jumped out of the tub.

126
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:51,867
I had to chase after them.

127
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,933
I ended up crashing
into a sack of oysters,

128
00:07:55,067 --> 00:07:56,867
and now look,
I'm all scraped up, Ma'am!

129
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Scraped up?

130
00:07:58,133 --> 00:07:59,200
Didang, you're making that up.

131
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,567
That didn't even happen!

132
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:01,300
Hey!

133
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:02,767
I don't lie, okay?

134
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:03,700
Want to see the wound?

135
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:05,000
Here, look!

136
00:08:05,133 --> 00:08:06,633
Hey, what are you doing?

137
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:08,567
I'm just showing the wound!

138
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:10,200
You're showing the wound?

139
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:11,567
- Yes! You're overreacting.
- Right here?

140
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,067
Dad, look at Didang!

141
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,233
It hit me right here.

142
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:15,067
Right, Sir Manuel?

143
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,567
You want to show Manuel, too?

144
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:20,333
Didang, will you stop it
already?

145
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,833
I'm just showing it!

146
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:22,967
Didang!

147
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,500
There's nothing even there!

148
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:26,700
- That's something else!
- Didang, I'll just have...

149
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:27,967
the eggplant omelet, please.

150
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:29,800
But I only showed
a bit of cleavage,

151
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:31,467
- and you already said no!
- Just the cleavage, okay?

152
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,500
Just?

153
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:35,833
Okay, here. Here's your omelet.

154
00:08:38,367 --> 00:08:42,233
<i>If Felma and Manuel get
back together with their kids,</i>

155
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:44,667
<i>you'll have no place
in Manuel's life.</i>

156
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:52,933
Jessica!

157
00:08:53,067 --> 00:08:53,867
Come here, quick!

158
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,333
Go join them!

159
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,267
Jessica, come eat with us!

160
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,667
Come on, sweetie,
have something to eat.

161
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:01,900
- Come on, dear.
- Come on.

162
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:03,700
It's okay. I'm still full.

163
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:08,233
Hey, want to see my wound?

164
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:09,867
I've got one on my leg, too,
Ma'am!

165
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:10,833
Here, I'll show you!

166
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:11,833
- On your leg?
- Yes, right here.

167
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:13,233
- It even reached your leg?
- Yes!

168
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:14,333
Look, here!

169
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:15,400
Don't strip!

170
00:09:15,533 --> 00:09:17,000
What exactly are
you trying to show?

171
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:18,733
Please excuse me.

172
00:09:18,867 --> 00:09:20,000
She's not interested either.

173
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:23,367
No one's interested, Didang!

174
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,233
- You keep trying to show it!
- Just eat already!

175
00:09:25,367 --> 00:09:26,633
- Exactly!
- Keep eating!

176
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:27,867
So what happened?

177
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:29,233
- Oh well...
- You fell face first?

178
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:29,967
Yeah! Totally fell.

179
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,267
I was covered in mud, Ma'am!

180
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,000
Good thing a handsome guy
helped me!

181
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:34,633
- A handsome guy, really?
- Yes!

182
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,000
With all the dramas in the ER,

183
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:40,833
the best one's got to be
the last one.

184
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:42,400
Which one? The one where the
husband dies,

185
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:44,733
but it turns out, he's not even
with the real wife?

186
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,367
Just the mistress?

187
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:49,333
Then the real wife shows up.

188
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:51,233
And the two get along.

189
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:53,233
- Right?
- Isn't that weird?

190
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:55,967
Well, in this day and age,

191
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:58,967
that kind of setup's not really
weird anymore, right?

192
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:02,567
I suppose the husband
really loves the mistress.

193
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:06,000
So the wife has no choice
but to accept it and share.

194
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,200
Goodness!

195
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:07,967
Right.

196
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,900
Or maybe the mistress is kinder,

197
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:13,767
and maybe she actually makes
the husband happy.

198
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:17,267
Or maybe she provides something
the wife can't.

199
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,133
Possible!

200
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:19,967
Right?

201
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:28,167
So it's okay for the mistress
to share with the wife?

202
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:33,000
What kind of twisted mind
do you all have?

203
00:10:34,733 --> 00:10:37,433
You're women, for heaven's sake!

204
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:39,167
She's the mistress!

205
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:41,000
The mistress,
no matter what you say,

206
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:41,700
is still the mistress.

207
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:43,233
A homewrecker.

208
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:45,800
Oh, affected much, Aunt?

209
00:10:45,933 --> 00:10:47,333
Allergic to mistresses?

210
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:50,267
True, we're not even
talking about you.

211
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,900
Oh wait, isn't her situation
kind of like that?

212
00:10:53,033 --> 00:10:55,567
But she's the legal wife.

213
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:58,167
That's why she can relate
so much.

214
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,233
- Right!
- True.

215
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,700
Right?

216
00:11:11,167 --> 00:11:12,267
- What now?
- Don't do it, friend!

217
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,967
I'll let it slide for now.

218
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:16,100
But if I hear any more
of your twisted opinions,

219
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:17,733
that's not the only thing
I'll throw at you.

220
00:11:17,867 --> 00:11:19,233
- What?
- Hazel, no!

221
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,333
Jessica?

222
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:46,600
Jessica, here.

223
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:49,167
Eat while the soup's still hot.

224
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:55,100
Sir.

225
00:11:55,233 --> 00:11:56,567
Thanks, Didang.

226
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,867
Okay.

227
00:12:01,633 --> 00:12:05,767
Dear, how are you feeling?

228
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:12,167
Come on, eat first
so your stomach warms up.

229
00:12:12,967 --> 00:12:15,000
Here.

230
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,567
The soup's still hot.

231
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:26,233
Dear, come on.

232
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:27,100
Tell me.

233
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:28,533
What's the problem?

234
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:32,833
Dad, just hold me.

235
00:12:32,967 --> 00:12:35,200
Please don't let go.

236
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:40,300
So, my youngest one
only wants affection.

237
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:47,067
Dad, please don't leave me,
okay?

238
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,100
Don't leave me.

239
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:50,767
Come on, dear.

240
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:53,367
I won't leave you.

241
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,900
Never.

242
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:57,767
Didn't I tell you this before?

243
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:01,300
And why would I leave you?

244
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:02,567
You're my child.

245
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:08,467
Sweetie, is this because
of the annulment?

246
00:13:10,667 --> 00:13:12,300
I'm sorry.

247
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:18,833
I didn't know it would
affect you like this.

248
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,167
But dear, I promise you,

249
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,000
nothing's going to change
between us, okay?

250
00:13:24,167 --> 00:13:28,433
The only thing that's ending
is my marriage to your mom.

251
00:13:28,567 --> 00:13:32,133
But my being your father?
That won't change.

252
00:13:32,267 --> 00:13:33,433
Okay?

253
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:34,800
No, it won't.

254
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:37,167
I love you so much, Dad.

255
00:13:40,233 --> 00:13:42,000
Dad, I love you.

256
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:46,100
I love you so much, too, dear.

257
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:49,100
I love you very much.

258
00:13:49,233 --> 00:13:50,467
Dad.

259
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:04,133
<i> Jessica, what's the update?</i>

260
00:14:04,267 --> 00:14:09,167
What are you doing to stop
your dad from filing the case?

261
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:12,300
<i>Don't tell me you're backing out
of our deal?</i>

262
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:15,233
<i>So, you still don't believe me?</i>

263
00:14:15,367 --> 00:14:17,300
<i>Look at yourself in the mirror.</i>

264
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:18,733
<i> Don't you wonder?</i>

265
00:14:18,867 --> 00:14:20,600
<i>You didn't get anything
from your dad.</i>

266
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:25,800
Maybe we should
make it official?

267
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:30,033
How about a DNA test?

268
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,767
Get a sample from your dad.

269
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:35,500
<i>Mom, do we really
need to go that far?</i>

270
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:36,500
<i> Yes!</i>

271
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:38,300
<i> So you'll finally believe.</i>

272
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:40,000
Mom, I won't do it.

273
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:41,500
<i> Why?</i>

274
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:43,700
<i> Afraid to know the truth?</i>

275
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:47,167
Mom, can you please
stop pushing me?

276
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:50,933
What are you and your mom
planning?

277
00:14:58,467 --> 00:14:59,700
Yes, Manuel.

278
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:04,167
I actually saw Jeffrey taking
the laing the other night.

279
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:06,433
I just didn't say anything.

280
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:08,200
Maybe he couldn't resist

281
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:10,867
since it was right
in front of him.

282
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,500
Maybe.

283
00:15:12,633 --> 00:15:15,233
I hope the same thing
happens to you.

284
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:18,800
Now that you and Jeff
are together here at home,

285
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:21,667
I hope he won't be able
to resist you either.

286
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:27,200
I hope he'll try to notice you,
talk to you.

287
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:28,167
Who knows?

288
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,767
Maybe this is the way
for both of you

289
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:33,267
to start forgiving each other.

290
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,467
I hope so, I really do.

291
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:37,667
While Jessica and I
are still here.

292
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:46,000
Oh, by the way, how is Jessica?

293
00:15:46,133 --> 00:15:47,300
That's another thing
I've been thinking about.

294
00:15:47,433 --> 00:15:48,267
That kid.

295
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:53,033
She's got some issues.

296
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,333
What is it?

297
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:57,333
Is it your hobby
to barge in here?

298
00:15:57,467 --> 00:15:59,100
Is that forbidden?

299
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:01,200
This is our house.

300
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:03,900
I can go anywhere, anytime.

301
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:08,233
And please, stop changing
the subject.

302
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,600
I heard you.

303
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:12,667
Your mom's up to something.

304
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:16,767
But what is it that
you don't want to do?

305
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:20,000
Stay out of it.

306
00:16:20,133 --> 00:16:22,033
It does not concern you.

307
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:23,633
I'm concerned.

308
00:16:23,767 --> 00:16:26,400
Because my mom's going
to get hurt again.

309
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:28,600
So please,
just tell me the truth.

310
00:16:28,733 --> 00:16:31,033
Can you just leave, Coleen?

311
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:31,567
How dare you!

312
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:32,733
Just say it already!

313
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:33,833
Let go!

314
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:34,800
Let go!

315
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,833
Tell me!

316
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:44,933
You're hurting me!

317
00:16:46,667 --> 00:16:48,467
- You won't admit it to me?
- Let me go!

318
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:51,033
Then say it in front
of Mom and Dad!

319
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:52,567
Coleen!

320
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:54,700
Was it about Coleen?

321
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:57,367
They still haven't reconciled?

322
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,800
No, it's about the annulment.

323
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:02,200
Let me go!

324
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:09,200
She's scared I'll leave her
if Hazel and I split up.

325
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:11,767
And her feelings are valid.

326
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,367
You just need to reassure
her that it won't happen.

327
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:17,100
There!

328
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:18,067
Admit it to them!

329
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,500
- Jessica!
- Let go of Jessica!

330
00:17:19,633 --> 00:17:20,433
Dear, that's enough!

331
00:17:20,567 --> 00:17:24,567
Coleen!

332
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:27,400
It's your daughter's fault, Dad.

333
00:17:27,533 --> 00:17:29,967
She's talking to her mom again.

334
00:17:30,100 --> 00:17:33,233
Dad, they're planning something.

335
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,167
Just tell them the truth,
Jessica!

336
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:36,067
You heard it, didn't you?

337
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,900
Then you say it!

338
00:17:38,033 --> 00:17:39,633
- Jessica!
- Don't be smart with me!

339
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:41,233
I said stop it!

340
00:17:41,367 --> 00:17:42,533
Paranoid!

341
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:45,400
You always assume the worst
and throw around accusations!

342
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:46,900
-Now you're talking back to me?
-Coleen!

343
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:48,700
- Jessica!
- Coleen!

344
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:49,767
- Coleen!
- Wait!

345
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:51,100
- That's enough!
- Jessica!

346
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:53,200
Coleen, stop it!

347
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,367
Jessica!

348
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:58,367
Jessica!

349
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,700
- Coleen?
- Coleen!

350
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:00,800
- Coleen!
- Coleen, dear!

351
00:18:04,933 --> 00:18:08,533
Come on, get up.

352
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:11,967
Jessica, are you okay?

353
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:15,533
What was Coleen talking about?

354
00:18:15,667 --> 00:18:20,000
When Mom found out
about the annulment...

355
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,967
she's been bugging me.

356
00:18:22,133 --> 00:18:26,033
She said once it goes through,
I'll live with her.

357
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:29,233
Dad, she's trying
to separate us.

358
00:18:29,367 --> 00:18:31,833
So I told her I didn't want to.

359
00:18:31,967 --> 00:18:33,700
Dad, I don't want that.

360
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,233
I'm serious, okay?

361
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,433
I'm getting fed up.

362
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:03,067
You and Jessica
used to be so close.

363
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,667
You should make up already.

364
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:08,767
Mom, it hurts.

365
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,033
Mom.

366
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:16,833
Do you know about the annulment

367
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:18,433
between Coleen's dad
and his wife?

368
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:23,033
Yes, son.

369
00:19:23,167 --> 00:19:25,000
But I'm staying out of it.

370
00:19:25,133 --> 00:19:28,733
I have no intention of getting
involved in their problem.

371
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:31,700
Is that the problem
you're talking about?

372
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:32,667
With your mom?

373
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:37,800
Dear, can you stop meeting

374
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:39,800
or talking to your mom
for a while?

375
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:43,300
It's not that easy, Dad.

376
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:44,533
Why?

377
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:50,267
Do you have a say in
your ex's decision?

378
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,300
I only know about it.

379
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:54,867
But I have nothing
to do with it.

380
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:55,833
It's his decision.

381
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:59,033
So why should I get
involved in that?

382
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:02,200
Mom, it's a mess again,
with that Hazel.

383
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:04,700
You're all dragged into it.

384
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,933
We're all affected.

385
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,400
You know, this is such a mess.

386
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:09,967
You guys are making it worse.

387
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:13,633
I came back here to this house
because I want peace.

388
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:16,033
And now this?

389
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:17,833
What? Is she threatening you?

390
00:20:22,300 --> 00:20:26,767
Dear, your mom won't leave
us alone, especially now.

391
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:31,100
I don't want your Aunt Felma
and your siblings

392
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:33,067
to get dragged into this.

393
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,800
I'm so embarrassed
by this already.

394
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:38,333
We're leaving as soon as we can.

395
00:20:40,767 --> 00:20:41,967
Do what you want.

396
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,833
Mom...

397
00:20:50,967 --> 00:20:54,800
If Dad's annulment
gets approved,

398
00:20:54,933 --> 00:20:56,533
will you get back together?

399
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:03,033
Yes, I can see the store now.

400
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:04,433
Sorry, I had to walk.

401
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:06,567
It's been raining a bit.

402
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:07,900
Oh, here it is. I see the sign.

403
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:08,900
Apartment for rent.

404
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:11,600
Is this the one?
That gate over there?

405
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:13,933
Yes, I'm here now.

406
00:21:14,067 --> 00:21:16,767
Yes, Mrs. Tulagan,
I'm here at the store.

407
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,767
Mrs. Tulagan?

408
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,400
Oh, hello!

409
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:26,567
Hi, hello.

410
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:27,533
You must be Sir Abel?

411
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:29,267
Yes, I'm the one you spoke with.

412
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,400
That's right.

413
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:32,333
Sir, I'm strict when it comes
to payments, okay?

414
00:21:32,467 --> 00:21:34,867
Three months' deposit,
one month advance.

415
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:35,967
Of course, understood.

416
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,500
Please don't offer it
to anyone else, okay?

417
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:38,433
We'll take it.

418
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:39,533
All right, all right.

419
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:41,733
But come inside first
so you can see the place.

420
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,267
That's also where I'll go
over the terms and requirements.

421
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:45,900
Sure, I'll follow.

422
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:46,833
Just need to call someone
real quick.

423
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:47,967
All right, I'll wait for you
inside.

424
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:49,800
- Yes, thank you.
- All right.

425
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:55,833
Hello, Manuel?

426
00:21:55,967 --> 00:21:59,067
Let Jessica know she doesn't
need to keep looking.

427
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,933
I found the perfect
place for both of you.

428
00:22:02,967 --> 00:22:04,233
Yes.

429
00:22:05,933 --> 00:22:06,900
Okay.

430
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:09,733
Okay, bye.

431
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:24,367
Manuel, what's the important
thing you need to tell me?

432
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:28,567
I just wanted to say goodbye.

433
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:32,867
Abel says the apartment
he found is ready.

434
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:37,400
Manuel...

435
00:22:37,533 --> 00:22:38,233
I'm sorry.

436
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:40,533
I'm sorry, Felma.

437
00:22:40,667 --> 00:22:44,533
I just remembered, the last time
I said goodbye to you...

438
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:47,833
<i> I'm afraid that later,</i>

439
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:50,233
<i>you might start looking
for someone else.</i>

440
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,600
<i> What are you talking about?</i>

441
00:22:52,733 --> 00:22:56,067
<i>With your beauty, why would
I look at anyone else?</i>

442
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,433
<i>My love, you're the only woman
in my life.</i>

443
00:22:58,567 --> 00:22:59,600
<i> You know that.</i>

444
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:00,500
<i> Is that true?</i>

445
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:02,067
<i> Promise?</i>

446
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,833
<i> I promise.</i>

447
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:05,867
But Felma, I will come back.

448
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,200
Okay?

449
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:09,133
I will come back for you
and the kids,

450
00:23:09,267 --> 00:23:11,233
and I will keep my promise
this time.

451
00:23:24,467 --> 00:23:27,633
It just feels so heavy, Felma.

452
00:23:27,767 --> 00:23:28,900
It's like...

453
00:23:29,033 --> 00:23:32,833
like our time together
was so short.

454
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:34,400
It went by so fast.

455
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:38,967
You know what I really loved?

456
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:42,333
That feeling of going
to bed with a smile.

457
00:23:42,467 --> 00:23:46,300
Because I knew I'd see you again
the next day.

458
00:23:48,267 --> 00:23:52,100
I loved that feeling
that when you'd leave,

459
00:23:52,233 --> 00:23:54,800
I'd wish time would move faster.

460
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:58,133
So it'd be afternoon
or evening again.

461
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:00,233
Because I knew you'd
be coming home.

462
00:24:00,367 --> 00:24:02,567
Even if we didn't talk,

463
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:04,767
just seeing you
was enough for me.

464
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:06,567
That already made me
so, so happy.

465
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:09,833
Manuel...

466
00:24:09,967 --> 00:24:11,667
Manuel, that's enough.

467
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:14,367
We're still going
to see each other.

468
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,767
You're just moving
to a different house.

469
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:18,900
It's not like you're
going abroad again.

470
00:24:37,367 --> 00:24:38,800
Jeffrey?

471
00:24:42,767 --> 00:24:43,633
Why are you talking to me?

472
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:44,400
Are we even close?

473
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:47,900
Sorry.

474
00:24:48,033 --> 00:24:49,567
I just couldn't sleep.

475
00:24:52,133 --> 00:24:54,600
I kept thinking about
my kid and her mother.

476
00:24:54,733 --> 00:24:56,067
I was going to ask Mom to
have coffee with me,

477
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,400
but she's not in her room.

478
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,133
How about you?
Why are you still up?

479
00:25:06,167 --> 00:25:08,033
Dad's not in his room either.

480
00:25:10,667 --> 00:25:12,433
I was looking for him, too.

481
00:25:26,467 --> 00:25:28,400
Dad, this place is really nice.

482
00:25:28,533 --> 00:25:31,033
Not too big,
not too small either.

483
00:25:31,167 --> 00:25:32,967
This is a prime location.

484
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:34,233
It's close to the hospital,

485
00:25:34,367 --> 00:25:36,600
the police station,
even the church,

486
00:25:36,767 --> 00:25:38,833
and there are convenience stores
nearby.

487
00:25:38,967 --> 00:25:40,233
So...

488
00:25:40,367 --> 00:25:42,233
Is this going to
be our new home?

489
00:25:42,367 --> 00:25:47,100
Oh, by the way, Ma'am,
I'm Mrs. Hazel Capistrano-Cruz.

490
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:48,200
I'm his wife.

491
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:50,200
And the other woman,
the mistress.

492
00:25:50,333 --> 00:25:51,700
Mom, when are you going to stop?

493
00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:52,733
Never.

494
00:25:52,867 --> 00:25:54,100
Not until I've taken you
and your father back.

495
00:25:54,233 --> 00:25:56,233
So help me,
if you want me to stop.

496
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:57,700
I will never help you.

497
00:25:57,833 --> 00:26:01,300
Maybe it's time your
father knows the truth.

498
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:03,900
What is it this time, Hazel?

499
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:04,867
There's something
you need to know.

500
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:05,867
Mom!

501
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,867
I want you to know
that Jessica...

502
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:08,500
No, please.

503
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:09,833
Let me tell him, Mom.

504
00:26:09,967 --> 00:26:10,900
Please, Mom.

505
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:12,133
What are you going to say?
